{
  "texts": [
    "These reasons cause inaccuracies (uncertainty) in labels to the training data decreasing the classification performance of the trained models.",
    "Furthermore, this uncertainty is often highly imbalanced since some of the classes are easier to identify than others. 7.",
    "Variation in image size and aspect ratio is very large.",
    "Most CNN architectures require that the input images have fixed dimensions and a typical approach in image classification is to first scale the images into a common size.",
    "This is not ideal in plankton recognition due to a very large variation in both the size and aspect ratio of plankton."
  ]
}